# SepGuard

An Agent-Based Data-Centric Machine Learning Framework for Early Sepsis Prediction using ICU Electronic Health Records.

## Overview

SepGuard is a machine learning framework designed for early sepsis prediction using ICU clinical data. The system focuses on adaptive preprocessing through a multi-agent architecture rather than relying only on complex models.

The framework introduces:

- DataProfiler Agent
- DecisionAgent
- RepairAgent
- Adaptive preprocessing pipeline
- SMOTE-based imbalance handling
- Logistic Regression and Random Forest models

The project demonstrates that data-centric preprocessing can significantly improve sepsis prediction performance.

---

## Features

- Agent-based preprocessing framework
- Missing value analysis
- Adaptive imputation
- Outlier-aware scaling
- Log transformation for skewed distributions
- SMOTE augmentation
- ROC-AUC based evaluation
- Threshold tuning for clinical sensitivity

---

## Dataset

This project uses ICU electronic health record datasets derived from:

- MIMIC-III
- PhysioNet Sepsis Challenge datasets

Note:
Raw datasets are not uploaded due to dataset licensing restrictions.

---

## System Architecture

The workflow consists of two stages:

1. Data Preprocessing and Quality Repair
2. Model Training and Risk Evaluation

### Pipeline

Raw Data
→ DataProfiler
→ DecisionAgent
→ RepairAgent
→ SMOTE
